main event: A civilian reported observing a silver elliptical object with fixed navigation lights near Philadelphia on September 24, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 15 to 20 minutes at around 2035 hours.,Witnesses reported that every vehicle in sight stopped and street lights went out during the sighting.,The object had no sound and passed overhead at a low altitude, casting bright reflections.,Witness described the object as making a rapid acceleration and disappearing after about 20 seconds.,The report noted that there was insufficient data for evaluation and no physical evidence was found.
